The paper discusses modularity in answer-set programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on disjunctive logic programs (DLPs) subject to stable-model semantics, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the compositionality of stable-model semantics, which is a topic in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the concept of modular equivalence, which is related to database systems (cs.DB).
